This paper discusses the use of unsupervised pre-training for natural language generation, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of neural networks (cs.NE) and the potential for image captioning applications (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of reinforcement learning (cs.AI) in some of the discussed methods. Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.CL and cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.CV.
